P3 — CI/CD ENGINEER
----------------------------------------------------------------
GOAL: GitHub Actions pipeline builds and pushes images to ECR.

STEP 1: Set GitHub Secrets
  GUI:
  - Go to your GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
  - Add secrets:
    AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID     → your IAM user access key
    AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY → your IAM user secret key
    AWS_REGION            → us-east-1
    AWS_ACCOUNT_ID        → your 12-digit AWS account ID

STEP 2: Create the GitHub Actions workflow
  CLI:
  mkdir -p .github/workflows
  cat > .github/workflows/ci.yml << 'EOF'
  name: Build and Push to ECR

  on:
    push:
      branches: [main]
    pull_request:
      branches: [main]

  env:
    AWS_REGION: us-east-1
    ECR_REGISTRY: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCOUNT_ID }}.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com

  jobs:
    build-and-push:
      runs-on: ubuntu-latest
      steps:
        - name: Checkout code
          uses: actions/checkout@v3

        - name: Set up JDK 17
          uses: actions/setup-java@v3
          with:
            java-version: '17'
            distribution: 'temurin'

        - name: Configure AWS credentials
          uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v2
          with:
            aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
            aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
            aws-region: ${{ env.AWS_REGION }}

        - name: Login to Amazon ECR
          id: login-ecr
          uses: aws-actions/amazon-ecr-login@v1

        - name: Build Docker images
          run: ./mvnw clean install -P buildDocker -DskipTests

        - name: Tag and push images to ECR
          run: |
            ACCOUNT_ID=${{ secrets.AWS_ACCOUNT_ID }}
            REGION=us-east-1
            SERVICES="config-server discovery-server customers-service vets-service visits-service api-gateway"
            for SERVICE in $SERVICES; do
              docker tag springcommunity/$SERVICE:latest \
                $ACCOUNT_ID.dkr.ecr.$REGION.amazonaws.com/petclinic/$SERVICE:latest
              docker push \
                $ACCOUNT_ID.dkr.ecr.$REGION.amazonaws.com/petclinic/$SERVICE:latest
            done
  EOF

STEP 3: Commit and push
  CLI:
  git add .github/workflows/ci.yml
  git commit -m "ci: add GitHub Actions build and push to ECR"
  git push origin main

STEP 4: Monitor the pipeline
  GUI:
  - Go to your GitHub repo → Actions tab
  - Watch the workflow run — it should go green
  - If it fails, click on the failed step to see the error log

STEP 5: Verify images in ECR
  CLI:
  aws ecr list-images --repository-name petclinic/config-server --region us-east-1

