P7 — DATABASE ADMINISTRATOR
----------------------------------------------------------------
GOAL: MySQL deployed and accessible to all backend services.

STEP 1: Create database secrets
  CLI:
  kubectl create secret generic petclinic-db-secret \
    --from-literal=mysql-root-password=petclinic-root \
    --from-literal=mysql-password=petclinic \
    --from-literal=mysql-user=petclinic \
    -n spring-petclinic

STEP 2: Create Helm values for MySQL (3 databases needed)
  CLI:
  # MySQL for customers
  cat > k8s/mysql-customers-values.yaml << 'EOF'
  auth:
    rootPassword: petclinic-root
    database: petclinic
    username: petclinic
    password: petclinic
  primary:
    persistence:
      size: 1Gi
  EOF

STEP 3: Deploy MySQL via Helm (one per service)
  CLI:
  helm install customers-db bitnami/mysql \
    --namespace spring-petclinic \
    --values k8s/mysql-customers-values.yaml

